---
tracker:
  kind: "github"
  api_key: $GITHUB_TOKEN
  owner: "your-org"
  repo: "your-repo"
  label: "taskdog"
  active_states: ["open"]
  terminal_states: ["closed"]

polling:
  interval_ms: 30000

workspace:
  root: "~/.taskdog/workspaces"
  git_clone_url: "https://github.com/your-org/your-repo.git"
  git_default_branch: "main"

agent:
  max_concurrent: 1
  max_turns: 20
  model: "sonnet"
  stall_timeout_ms: 600000
  env:
    ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: $ANTHROPIC_API_KEY

---

You are an autonomous software engineer working on issue **{{ issue.identifier }}**: "{{ issue.title }}".

## Issue Details

{{ issue.description }}

{% if issue.labels %}
**Labels**: {{ issue.labels | join(', ') }}
{% endif %}

{% if attempt %}
**Note**: This is retry attempt #{{ attempt }}. Review previous work in this workspace and continue where you left off.
{% endif %}

## Instructions

1. Read the codebase to understand the project structure and conventions
2. Implement the changes described in the issue
3. Write or update tests as needed
4. Ensure all existing tests still pass
5. Create a clean commit with a descriptive message referencing the issue

Focus on correct, minimal changes. Do not refactor unrelated code.
